FBIS4-9480 "dreeu080__a94049" FBIS-EEU-94-080-A Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 ANNEX Slovakia APR, AD Merge To Form New Party APR, AD Merge To Form New Party AU2304173894 Prague CTK in English 1203 GMT 23 Apr 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2304173894 Prague CTK English BFN [Text] Bratislava, April 23 (CTK) -- A new political party -- the Democratic Union of Slovakia (DEUS) was founded today through a merger of the Alternative of Political Realism (APR) of Slovak Premier Jozef Moravcik and the Alliance of Slovak Democrats (AD) of former Foreign Minister Milan Knazko. The two parties' delegates agreed to the move at a merger assembly in Bratislava. Moravcik has been proposed DEUS chairman, Knazko is likely to become the first deputy chairman. Other deputy chairmen would be Deputy Premier Roman Kovac, Finance Minister Rudolf Filkus, and Viliam Vaskovic, vice-president of the presidium of the National Property Fund (FNM). Voting on the above candidates is planned for the afternoon. DEUS intends to push for the interests of people who want to live in a civic society, which respects civic freedoms, pluralist democracy, the market economy and freedom of trade. According to a recent poll, the APR and the AD together have 9 per cent of electoral preferences, and are the third strongest political grouping in Slovakia, after the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) and the Democratic Left Party (SDL).
